    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>A recently proposed temporal correlation-based- network framework applied on financial markets called Struc- tural Entropy has prompted us to utilize it as a means of analysis for COVID-19 fatalities across countries. Our observation on the resemblance of volatility of fluctuations of daily novel coronavirus related number of deaths to the daily stock exchange returns suggests the applicability of this approach.</jats:p>",
